American Association of Colleges of Podiatric Medicine (AACPM) is the collective union for the nine colleges of podiatric medicine in the United States and the more than 200 hospitals and institutions that offer postdoctoral training in podiatric medicine. Based in Rockville, Maryland, the AACPM serves as a forum and association for the promotion and betterment of podiatric medical education in the U.S. The AACPM also manages the AACPMAS (American Association of Colleges of Podiatric Medicine Application Service), the online application service which allows potential podiatric medical students to apply to the nine colleges of podiatric medicine in the U.S.
